<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<p>This guidance summarises information sent from the Department of Health and Social Care (DHSC) to supply businesses in October 2019 about:</p>

<ul>
  <li>a new DHSC unit offering specialist guidance to get supply businesses ready for the new customs and border arrangements</li>
  <li>freight capacity the government now has away from the busiest ports</li>
  <li>a fast freight service to get priority goods into the UK quickly</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="trader-readiness-hotline">Trader readiness ‘hotline’</h2>

<p>Traders in the medical supply industry can ask the government for advice on the new customs and border rules and processes that would start immediately following a no-deal Brexit:</p>

<ol>
  <li>email your queries to: <a href="mailto:betraderready@dhsc.gov.uk">betraderready@dhsc.gov.uk</a>
</li>
  <li>a specialist from the trader readiness team will call or email you back</li>
</ol>

<p>You’ll get the latest information and practical guidance on how to prepare for Brexit.</p>

<p>This is dedicated help for the health and social care sector. The teams will work closely with HMRC and the Border Delivery Group.</p>

<h2 id="government-secured-freight-capacity">Government-secured freight capacity</h2>

<p>The government now has space for important goods on alternative routes away from the busiest terminals and ports.</p>

<p>This is to help deal with the expected disruption to the UK’s most heavily used entry points for goods in the months immediately after Brexit.</p>

<p>All companies moving priority products, known as <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/critical-goods-for-government-secured-freight-capacity">category 1 goods</a>, into the UK can use the government-secured freight capacity if they need to. This includes all medicines, medical devices and clinical products.</p>

<p>The Department for Transport now has <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/government-signs-contracts-securing-continued-flow-of-vital-medicines-after-brexit">contracts with shipping companies</a> able to move thousands of HGVs a week through different routes and terminals.</p>

<p>To use this capacity, companies will have to register and then buy tickets in advance. It is not possible to turn up at the border and use the service without prior booking.</p>

<h2 id="express-freight-service">Express freight service</h2>

<p>DHSC will offer a service that ships small amounts of medical supplies into the UK quickly, at short notice.</p>

<p>Suppliers can only use this if at least one of the following happens:</p>

<ul>
  <li>you have problems with your own contingency plans</li>
  <li>there is an urgent need for specific medical devices or medicines</li>
</ul>

<p>To use this last-minute service, the government needs to have and verify a range of information from suppliers ahead of time. You should register now.</p>

<h2 id="how-to-register-for-the-government-secured-freight-capacity-and-express-freight-service">How to register for the government-secured freight capacity and express freight service</h2>

<p>You can register to use both the fast shipping service and the freight capacity through one system. The link to register was sent in an email to all eligible companies on 8 October 2019. If you need this link, see the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/how-medical-supply-businesses-can-use-government-help-to-manage-brexit#contacts">contacts</a> section below. To register:</p>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>click the link and complete the online form – we recommend that staff working on the supply chain fill out this form</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>you will get an access code within 2 working days of registering</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>from late October you can use the access code to buy freight space</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>to use the government-secured freight capacity, tell your hauliers to complete the haulier registration process – more guidance on this will be available later in October</p>
  </li>
</ol>

<p>The government will use your registration details to contact you about the ticketing process.</p>

<p>Registering doesn’t commit you to buying this capacity.</p>

<p>If you are not sure or don’t think you’ll need to use government-secured capacity, you should still register. You can leave a comment during the registration process to tell us.</p>

<p>If you don’t register now, you can still register later. However, we encourage you to register early to help with ongoing contingency planning.</p>

<h2 id="contacts">Contacts</h2>

<p>If you have any questions, or you need the link to register for the freight services, you can contact the relevant government team for your sector:</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>Medicines: <a href="mailto:medicinescontingencyplanning@dhsc.gov.uk">medicinescontingencyplanning@dhsc.gov.uk</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Medical Devices and Clinical Consumables: <a href="mailto:mdcc-contingencyplanning@dhsc.gov.uk">mdcc-contingencyplanning@dhsc.gov.uk</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Clinical Trials: <a href="mailto:ctcontingencyplanning@dhsc.gov.uk">ctcontingencyplanning@dhsc.gov.uk</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Vaccines and Countermeasures: <a href="mailto:immunisation-mb@dhsc.gov.uk">immunisation-mb@dhsc.gov.uk</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Blood and Transplants: <a href="mailto:transplants@dhsc.gov.uk">transplants@dhsc.gov.uk</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Non-Clinical Goods and Services: <a href="mailto:contractreview@dhsc.gov.uk">contractreview@dhsc.gov.uk</a></p>
  </li>
</ul>

<h2 id="related-guidance">Related guidance</h2>

<p>See more guidance on <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/businesses-supplying-medicines-and-medical-devices-what-to-expect-on-day-one-of-a-no-deal-scenario">how medical supply businesses can prepare for Brexit</a>.</p>
